main event: Multiple people reported seeing two bright, fast-moving lights in the sky over Baltimore, Maryland on May 27, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as 'terrific speed', 'floated', and 'bobbed'.
There were two independent observations of the objects, one at 2230 hours and one at 2330 hours.
The objects made no noticeable sound, which was considered strange since sounds from a nearby stadium could be heard.
An unidentified T-6 aircraft was also spotted in the area around the same time.
Weather conditions were clear with good visibility at the time of the sightings.
witnesses: multiple civilian witnesses, including Leonard Jones and Richard Adam Bosse
photographs: no photographs included in the report
